        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>124300</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>σ</orig><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/><orig>α</orig><space quantity="1" unit="character"/><orig>ισθι</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w lemma="ὅδε">τόδε</w> <space unit="character" atLeast="6"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>Apart from <foreign xml:lang="grc">τόδε</foreign> ('this') at line 2, the text is quite unclear. The imperative <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἴσθι</foreign> is only a mere possibility
               and does not help to determine a precise text-type. Anyway, a reading with a name in <foreign xml:lang="grc">σθένης</foreign> does not seem possible, because the last readable letter is no epsilon.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
